observations.recommendation:
In view thereof, we recommended management to:
Direct the Municipal Accountant to observe the perpetual inventory method of recording purchases of supplies and materials and to draw the necessary adjusting entries to present the correct balances of the affected inventory asset and expense accounts;
Require the Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjusting entries for the misclassified transactions to reflect the correct balances of the affected accounts;
Observe the additional information required by PPSAS that is not shown on the face of the financial statements but relevant to an understanding;
Require the Municipal Accountant to effect the necessary adjustment on the variances noted to correct the reported balances of the affected accounts in the Financial Statements.

We recommended management to ensure that the requisites for the bidding of infrastructure contracts provided in Section 17.4 of the Revised IRR of RA 9184 such as the detailed engineering investigations, surveys and designs for the project, have been sufficiently carried out and duly approved to ensure that all the undertakings are economically and efficiently carried out to protect the interest of the government; and:
Require the Engineering Office key personnel to closely monitor the project implementation and ensure that the project is on schedule;
Ensure the strict observance of the construction period as stipulated in the Contract and Notice to Proceed and strictly adhere to prescribed rules and regulations regarding a delay in completion of infrastructure projects;
Act with dispatch in resolving the existing issue/problems that are currently hampering/delaying the implementation and/or completion of projects.

We recommended that the Municipal Treasurer to:
Coordinate with the Municipal Assessor’s Office and devise a comprehensive strategy primarily focused on the collection of delinquent property taxes to reduce the outstanding amount of delinquencies substantially;
Request sufficient funding for plantilla position and for other needs of the office to facilitate effective property tax collection, monitoring and assessment;
Refer the matter of ancestral domain to the provincial government of Compostela Valley to notify them of the problem and come up with an appropriate strategy or solution on the matter; and
Follow-up the progress of the Program to Segregate Titles for CLOA owners with the Department of Agrarian Reform.

We recommended the following courses of action: 

Require the Municipal Accountant to effect the necessary adjustment on the omissions/errors to correct the reported balances of the affected accounts in the Financial Statements;

Prepare a reconciliation statement for the discrepancies noted in the balances of Due to other NGAs account vis-a-vis NGAs records and effect the necessary adjusting entries, if any and coordinate or make representation to NGAs Accountant to settle the variance.;

Observe the additional information required by PPSAS that is not shown on the face of the financial statements but relevant to an understanding.
